    <bullet>
        What are events?
    </bullet>

    <bullet indent="indent-star">
        Something that happens to which you might want to respond
    </bullet>

    <bullet>
        How do we tell the computer that we want to respond to the event?
    </bullet>

    <bullet indent="indent-star">
        Register the events that require a response.
    </bullet>

    <bullet>
        On what objects can we register events?
    </bullet>

    <bullet indent="indent-star">
        Events can be registered on the <b>window</b>, <b>document</b>, or on an element.
    </bullet>

    <bullet>
        What method do we use to register and event listener on a target?
    </bullet>

    <bullet indent="indent-star">
        target.addEventListener(type, listener);
    </bullet>

    <bullet>
        What are some event types?
    </bullet>

    <bullet indent="indent-star">
        keyup, click, change, and submit
    </bullet>

    <bullet>
        What method do we use to remove an event listener?
    </bullet>

    <bullet indent="indent-star">
        target.removeEventListener(type, listener);
    </bullet>

